Nita Talbot https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nita_Talbot 0 Nita Talbot (born Anita Sokol; August 8, 1930) is an American actress. Talbot was a leading lady who spent the first decade or so of her career playing "slick chicks" and sharp-witted career girls. Talbot received an Emmy Award nomination for Best Supporting Actress in a Comedy Series for the 1967–68 season of Hogan's Heroes.
